<subSubSection id="C31BE28D77EFFF14FF44A3D7922EFD32" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BBEB10677EFFF14FF44A3D793C7FE87" blockId="184.[151,1437,151,1040]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis id="B9756D1477EFFF14FF44A3D79124FF4F" bold="true" box="[199,345,188,213]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Description.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="133AAD8377EFFF14FEE5A3D791B9FF4F" box="[358,452,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 115" captionStartId="183.[151,250,1908,1930]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,423,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@183.[151,1436,423,1886]" captionTargetPageId="183" captionText="FIGURE 115. Epipolasis tubulata sp. nov., a, habitus of holotype RMNH Por. 9965, a 1, habitus of paratype RMNH Por. 10549 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, light microscopic image of tangential halichondrioid ectosomal skeleton, c, ditto of cross section of peripheral skeleton, d – g, SEM images of the spicules, d, large oxeote style, d 1, details of d, e, small oxeote style, e 1, details of e, f, trichodragma, g, individual raphide, g 1, detail of hooked end of g." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273065/files/figure.png" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Fig. 115</figureCitation>
a) Sponge forms low thick-walled tubes, diameter of the larger tube 
<quantity id="4CF91CE377EFFF14FB3AA3D7957AFF4E" box="[1209,1287,188,213]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" unit="cm" value="1.5">1.5 cm</quantity>
, height 
<quantity id="4CF91CE377EFFF14FADDA3D795E5FF4E" box="[1374,1432,188,212]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
. Largest tube opening 
<quantity id="4CF91CE377EFFF14FE13A38B91AEFF6D" box="[400,467,224,248]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
in diameter. Surface smooth, but irregular around the oscules. Color greyish brown. Consistency compressible. The smaller 
<typeStatus id="54BA0FA477EFFF14FDD6A26E92C8FE87" box="[597,693,261,285]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">paratype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation id="133AAD8377EFFF14FD47A26F9358FE87" box="[708,805,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 115" captionStartId="183.[151,250,1908,1930]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,423,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@183.[151,1436,423,1886]" captionTargetPageId="183" captionText="FIGURE 115. Epipolasis tubulata sp. nov., a, habitus of holotype RMNH Por. 9965, a 1, habitus of paratype RMNH Por. 10549 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, light microscopic image of tangential halichondrioid ectosomal skeleton, c, ditto of cross section of peripheral skeleton, d – g, SEM images of the spicules, d, large oxeote style, d 1, details of d, e, small oxeote style, e 1, details of e, f, trichodragma, g, individual raphide, g 1, detail of hooked end of g." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273065/files/figure.png" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Fig. 115</figureCitation>
a1) is similar.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBEB10677EFFF14FF44A24C9226FE37" blockId="184.[151,1437,151,1040]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis id="B9756D1477EFFF14FF44A24C9148FEDA" bold="true" box="[199,309,295,320]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Skeleton.</emphasis>
The surface (
<figureCitation id="133AAD8377EFFF14FE4CA24C9253FEDA" box="[463,558,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 115" captionStartId="183.[151,250,1908,1930]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,423,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@183.[151,1436,423,1886]" captionTargetPageId="183" captionText="FIGURE 115. Epipolasis tubulata sp. nov., a, habitus of holotype RMNH Por. 9965, a 1, habitus of paratype RMNH Por. 10549 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, light microscopic image of tangential halichondrioid ectosomal skeleton, c, ditto of cross section of peripheral skeleton, d – g, SEM images of the spicules, d, large oxeote style, d 1, details of d, e, small oxeote style, e 1, details of e, f, trichodragma, g, individual raphide, g 1, detail of hooked end of g." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273065/files/figure.png" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Fig. 115</figureCitation>
b) is a halichondrioid tangential crust of intercrossing spicule tracts and single spicules, 2–10 spicules in diameter. This is carried by choanosomal spicule tracts (
<figureCitation id="133AAD8377EFFF14FBECA22794A8FEFF" box="[1135,1237,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 115" captionStartId="183.[151,250,1908,1930]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,423,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@183.[151,1436,423,1886]" captionTargetPageId="183" captionText="FIGURE 115. Epipolasis tubulata sp. nov., a, habitus of holotype RMNH Por. 9965, a 1, habitus of paratype RMNH Por. 10549 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, light microscopic image of tangential halichondrioid ectosomal skeleton, c, ditto of cross section of peripheral skeleton, d – g, SEM images of the spicules, d, large oxeote style, d 1, details of d, e, small oxeote style, e 1, details of e, f, trichodragma, g, individual raphide, g 1, detail of hooked end of g." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273065/files/figure.png" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Fig. 115</figureCitation>
c), likewise 2–10 spicules in cross section, surrounded by a largely confused mass of single spicules and numerous single raphides, partially arranged in thin trichodragmas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBEB10677EFFF14FF44A2DC9355FE4A" blockId="184.[151,1437,151,1040]" box="[199,808,439,464]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis id="B9756D1477EFFF14FF44A2DC914DFE4A" bold="true" box="[199,304,439,464]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Spicules.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="133AAD8377EFFF14FEBCA2DC91DDFE4A" box="[319,416,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 115" captionStartId="183.[151,250,1908,1930]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,423,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@183.[151,1436,423,1886]" captionTargetPageId="183" captionText="FIGURE 115. Epipolasis tubulata sp. nov., a, habitus of holotype RMNH Por. 9965, a 1, habitus of paratype RMNH Por. 10549 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, light microscopic image of tangential halichondrioid ectosomal skeleton, c, ditto of cross section of peripheral skeleton, d – g, SEM images of the spicules, d, large oxeote style, d 1, details of d, e, small oxeote style, e 1, details of e, f, trichodragma, g, individual raphide, g 1, detail of hooked end of g." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273065/files/figure.png" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Figs 115</figureCitation>
d–g) Oxeote styles, trichodragmas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBEB10677EFFF14FF44A2B79237FDA7" blockId="184.[151,1437,151,1040]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">
Oxeotes, style-like, smooth, slightly fusiform, usually somewhat curved, with a faint subapical constriction, in two distinct size categories, (1) larger (
<figureCitation id="133AAD8377EFFF14FDE4A29492AEFD82" box="[615,723,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 115" captionStartId="183.[151,250,1908,1930]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,423,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@183.[151,1436,423,1886]" captionTargetPageId="183" captionText="FIGURE 115. Epipolasis tubulata sp. nov., a, habitus of holotype RMNH Por. 9965, a 1, habitus of paratype RMNH Por. 10549 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, light microscopic image of tangential halichondrioid ectosomal skeleton, c, ditto of cross section of peripheral skeleton, d – g, SEM images of the spicules, d, large oxeote style, d 1, details of d, e, small oxeote style, e 1, details of e, f, trichodragma, g, individual raphide, g 1, detail of hooked end of g." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273065/files/figure.png" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Figs 115</figureCitation>
d,d1), 462– 
<emphasis id="B9756D1477EFFF14FCD0A2949300FD82" box="[851,893,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">601</emphasis>
–618 
<date id="FFBF97C677EFFF14FC43A16B9388FD82" box="[960,1013,512,536]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" value="2012-10">x 12</date>
– 
<emphasis id="B9756D1477EFFF14FB87A2949448FD82" box="[1028,1077,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">16.3</emphasis>
–19 µm, and (2) smaller (
<figureCitation id="133AAD8377EFFF14FAE9A29490BBFDA7" captionStart="FIGURE 115" captionStartId="183.[151,250,1908,1930]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,423,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@183.[151,1436,423,1886]" captionTargetPageId="183" captionText="FIGURE 115. Epipolasis tubulata sp. nov., a, habitus of holotype RMNH Por. 9965, a 1, habitus of paratype RMNH Por. 10549 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, light microscopic image of tangential halichondrioid ectosomal skeleton, c, ditto of cross section of peripheral skeleton, d – g, SEM images of the spicules, d, large oxeote style, d 1, details of d, e, small oxeote style, e 1, details of e, f, trichodragma, g, individual raphide, g 1, detail of hooked end of g." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273065/files/figure.png" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Figs 115</figureCitation>
e,e1), 192– 
<emphasis id="B9756D1477EFFF14FEBEA14F911AFDA7" box="[317,359,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">286</emphasis>
–324 
<date id="FFBF97C677EFFF14FE26A14E91B5FDA7" box="[421,456,548,573]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">x 5</date>
– 
<emphasis id="B9756D1477EFFF14FE54A14F9187FDA6" box="[471,506,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">7.4</emphasis>
–9 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBEB10677EFFF14FF44A12C922EFD32" blockId="184.[151,1437,151,1040]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">
Raphides, partially in thin trichodragmas (
<figureCitation id="133AAD8377EFFF14FD47A12C9357FDFA" box="[708,810,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 115" captionStartId="183.[151,250,1908,1930]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,423,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@183.[151,1436,423,1886]" captionTargetPageId="183" captionText="FIGURE 115. Epipolasis tubulata sp. nov., a, habitus of holotype RMNH Por. 9965, a 1, habitus of paratype RMNH Por. 10549 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, light microscopic image of tangential halichondrioid ectosomal skeleton, c, ditto of cross section of peripheral skeleton, d – g, SEM images of the spicules, d, large oxeote style, d 1, details of d, e, small oxeote style, e 1, details of e, f, trichodragma, g, individual raphide, g 1, detail of hooked end of g." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273065/files/figure.png" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Fig. 115</figureCitation>
f), but many raphides (
<figureCitation id="133AAD8377EFFF14FBC7A12C94D7FDFA" box="[1092,1194,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 115" captionStartId="183.[151,250,1908,1930]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,423,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@183.[151,1436,423,1886]" captionTargetPageId="183" captionText="FIGURE 115. Epipolasis tubulata sp. nov., a, habitus of holotype RMNH Por. 9965, a 1, habitus of paratype RMNH Por. 10549 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, light microscopic image of tangential halichondrioid ectosomal skeleton, c, ditto of cross section of peripheral skeleton, d – g, SEM images of the spicules, d, large oxeote style, d 1, details of d, e, small oxeote style, e 1, details of e, f, trichodragma, g, individual raphide, g 1, detail of hooked end of g." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273065/files/figure.png" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">
Fig. 
<quantity id="4CF91CE377EFFF14FB03A12C94D7FDFA" box="[1152,1194,583,608]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.15" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" unit="g" value="115.0">115</quantity>
</figureCitation>
g) are strewn singly throughout the skeleton; provided with a lanceolate hook at both ends (
<figureCitation id="133AAD8377EFFF14FC5AA1079442FD1F" box="[985,1087,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 115" captionStartId="183.[151,250,1908,1930]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,423,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@183.[151,1436,423,1886]" captionTargetPageId="183" captionText="FIGURE 115. Epipolasis tubulata sp. nov., a, habitus of holotype RMNH Por. 9965, a 1, habitus of paratype RMNH Por. 10549 (scale bar = 1 cm), b, light microscopic image of tangential halichondrioid ectosomal skeleton, c, ditto of cross section of peripheral skeleton, d – g, SEM images of the spicules, d, large oxeote style, d 1, details of d, e, small oxeote style, e 1, details of e, f, trichodragma, g, individual raphide, g 1, detail of hooked end of g." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273065/files/figure.png" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">
Fig. 
<quantity id="4CF91CE377EFFF14FB92A1079442FD1F" box="[1041,1087,620,645]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.15" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" unit="g" value="115.0">115</quantity>
</figureCitation>
g1), 76– 
<emphasis id="B9756D1477EFFF14FB19A10794CBFD1E" box="[1178,1206,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">87</emphasis>
–114 x 0.3–0.4 µm; trichodragmas up to 20 µm in diameter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31BE28D77EFFF14FF44A1DF9316FD57" box="[199,875,692,717]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BBEB10677EFFF14FF44A1DF9316FD57" blockId="184.[151,1437,151,1040]" box="[199,875,692,717]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis id="B9756D1477EFFF14FF44A1DF918FFD57" bold="true" box="[199,498,692,717]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Distribution and ecology.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F316F19677EFFF14FE7AA1DF922DFD56" box="[505,592,692,716]" name="Guyana" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Guyana</collectingCountry>
Shelf, at 
<quantity id="4CF91CE377EFFF14FD3FA1DF9362FD56" box="[700,799,692,717]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.75" metricValueMax="6.8" metricValueMin="6.7" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" unit="m" value="67.5" valueMax="68.0" valueMin="67.0">67–68 m</quantity>
depth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31BE28D77EFFF14FF44A1BC93EEFD6A" box="[199,915,727,752]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BBEB10677EFFF14FF44A1BC93EEFD6A" blockId="184.[151,1437,151,1040]" box="[199,915,727,752]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis id="B9756D1477EFFF14FF44A1BC9133FD6A" bold="true" box="[199,334,727,752]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name refers to the tubular shape of the sponge.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31BE28D77EFFF14FF44A19792F2FB8A" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BBEB10677EFFF14FF44A19792F2FB8A" blockId="184.[151,1437,151,1040]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">
<materialsCitation id="3B69BB5B77EFFF14FF44A19792F2FB8A" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1424726533" collectingDate="1600-10-29" location="Central West" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Central West" typeStatus="holotype">
<emphasis id="B9756D1477EFFF14FF44A1979146FC8F" bold="true" box="[199,315,764,789]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus assignment is tentative. At first the species was assigned to the axinellid genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C01CA8577EFFF14FF14A04A916AFCA2" box="[151,279,801,824]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Dragmaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9756D1477EFFF14FF14A04A916AFCA2" box="[151,279,801,824]" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Dragmaxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(cf. above), because of the combination of smooth stylote spicules with trichodragmas. However, the clear division into a larger and a smaller category of megascleres added to the tangential halichondrioid ectosomal skeleton, precludes membership of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C01CA8577EFFF14FD1BA002936AFC1A" box="[664,791,873,896]" class="Demospongiae" family="Axinellidae" genus="Dragmaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9756D1477EFFF14FD1BA002936AFC1A" box="[664,791,873,896]" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Dragmaxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. So far, 
<taxonomicName id="4C01CA8577EFFF14FCFBA00C9393FC1A" box="[888,1006,871,896]" class="Demospongiae" family="Halichondriidae" genus="Epipolasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9756D1477EFFF14FCFBA00C9393FC1A" box="[888,1006,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Epipolasis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been limited to species with large and small oxeas, although stylote modifications are reported in the 
<typeStatus id="54BA0FA477EFFF14FC15A0E693BBFC3F" box="[918,966,909,933]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C01CA8577EFFF14FBACA0E690AFFC52" authority="Wilson, 1925" authorityName="Wilson" authorityYear="1925" class="Demospongiae" family="Halichondriidae" genus="Spongosorites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="suluensis">
<emphasis id="B9756D1477EFFF14FBACA0E69541FC3F" box="[1071,1340,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Spongosorites suluensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF90CCF777EFFF14FAC6A0E790AFFC52" author="Wilson" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" refString="Wilson, H. V. (1925) Silicious and horny sponges collected by the U. S. Fisheries Steamer ' Albatross' during the Philippine Expedition, 1907 - 10. In: Contributions to the biology of the Philippine Archipelago and adjacent regions. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, 100 (2, part 4), 273 - 532." type="journal article" year="1925">Wilson, 1925</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. There is one other 
<taxonomicName id="4C01CA8577EFFF14FE36A0C49256FC52" box="[437,555,943,968]" class="Demospongiae" family="Halichondriidae" genus="Epipolasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9756D1477EFFF14FE36A0C49256FC52" box="[437,555,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Epipolasis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the 
<collectingRegion id="49C57FE477EFFF14FDFFA0C49370FC5D" box="[636,781,943,968]" isEnumeration="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Central West</collectingRegion>
Atlantic, 
<taxonomicName id="4C01CA8577EFFF14FCFCA0DA95E5FC52" authority="Diaz, Pomponi &amp; Van Soest, 1993" authorityName="Diaz, Pomponi &amp; Van Soest" authorityYear="1993" box="[895,1432,943,968]" class="Demospongiae" family="Halichondriidae" genus="Epipolasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="profunda">
<emphasis id="B9756D1477EFFF14FCFCA0DA9478FC52" box="[895,1029,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">E. profunda</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF90CCF777EFFF14FB8DA0DB95E5FC52" author="Diaz" box="[1038,1432,943,968]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" refString="Diaz, M. C., Pomponi, S. A. &amp; Van Soest, R. W. M. (1993) A systematic revision of the central West Atlantic Halichondrida (Demospongiae, Porifera). Part III: Description of valid species. In: Uriz, M. - J. &amp; Rutzler, K. (Eds.), Recent Advances in Ecology and Systematics of Sponges. Scientia Marina, 57 (4), 283 - 306." type="journal article" year="1993">Díaz, Pomponi &amp; Van Soest, 1993</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but this has much larger spicules (up to 
<date id="FFBF97C677EFFF14FDD9A0BF92B6FC76" box="[602,715,980,1005]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" value="1600-10-29">
<collectingDate id="EFFB6E2E77EFFF14FDD9A0BF92B6FC76" box="[602,715,980,1005]" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" value="1600-10-29">1600 x 29</collectingDate>
</date>
µm), which are predominantly proper oxeas; trichodragmas are only half as long as those of the new species.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
